[1] California (San Diego County)
Date: Wed 30 Apr 2014
Source: KUSI News [edited]
http://www.kusi.com/story/25389578/county-pertussis-cases-up-nearly-600-percent-over-last-year


There have been 298 pertussis cases reported in San Diego County [California] in 2014, nearly 6 times the 53 reported this time in 2013, the county Health and Human Services Agency reported this week [week of 28 Apr 2014]. There were 18 cases of the illness, also known as whooping cough, reported last week [week of 21 Apr 2014], according to the agency. Infants not yet fully vaccinated are at highest risk for complications.

"Pertussis has shown no signs of slowing down and this high level of activity should be a concern for parents and caregivers," said Dr. Wilma Wooten, the county public health officer. "The vaccine's effectiveness lessens over time so it's very important that adults get their booster shots and that they make sure their children have the necessary doses of the vaccine at the recommended ages."

