[4] Maine (York County)
Date: Wed 30 Apr 2014
Source: WMTW [edited]
http://m.wmtw.com/health/whooping-cough-cases-on-the-rise/25740834


Whooping cough cases are on the rise in Kennebunk [York County, Maine] and parents are on alert. A total of 6 cases have been reported this week [week of 28 Apr 2014]. The superintendent sent an email to parents letting them know what's being done to keep kids at school, but it also talks about how prevention starts at home. "We don't want to raise concern about issues that aren't significant. We don't want to create hysteria, but it is important to share when there are situations where there is a contagious disease that we want folks to be aware of," said Superintendent Andrew Dolloff.

This week, a student at the Middle School of the Kennebunks contracted the disease, making it the 6th case district-wide and the 4th at the school. Each confirmed case means a mandatory 5 days away from the school to help stop the spread.

[Byline: Lindsay Liepman]

